    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can help you draft a rejection email that's both professional and kind. Here's a sample:\n\n\"Dear [Candidate Name],\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the status of your application for the Senior Developer position at [Company Name]. We were truly impressed by your technical skills and experience, and we were excited to learn more about your qualifications. Unfortunately, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose skills and fit align more closely with our current needs.\n\nPlease know that this decision was not made lightly, and we were genuinely impressed by your abilities. We appreciate the time you took to interview with us and share your insights with our team. We wish you the best of luck in your job search and are confident that you will find a role that's a great fit for you.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\"\n\nYou can modify this to fit your company's tone and style, but I hope this gives you a good starting point. Remember to keep it professional, kind, and clear, just like you mentioned.",
